    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>COVID-19 is an ongoing pandemic with a devastating impact on public health. Acute neurological symptoms have been reported after a COVID-19 diagnosis, however there is no data available on the long-term neurological symptoms. Using a prospective registry of hospitalized COVID-19 patients, we assessed the neurological assessments (including functional, cognitive and psychiatric assessments) of several hospitalized patients at 3 months. Our main finding is that 71% of the patients still experienced neurological symptoms at 3 months and the most common symptoms being fatigue (42%) and PTSD (29%). 64% of the patients report pain symptoms we well. Cognitive symptoms were found in 12%. Our preliminary findings suggests the importance of investigating long-term and rationalizes the need for further studies investigating the neurologic outcomes after COVID-19.</jats:p>",
